<br>
To the guys claiming they made 10000000 dollars/plats, most of them are full of shit. The only profitable auto macro was back before the bow nerf, some made a few thousand bucks then, that's about it.<br>
<br>
The best way to make money nowdays is setting up 3-5 PCs and just farm high yield cash items. Use macro to raise foraging and stuff, not making serious money.<br>
<br>
Pedi you said the guy would just put up afk when a GM zones in? that's pretty cool, I havent been following eq hacks for a while, but from my understanding he will need a version of showeq to detect the GM zoning in, then a script/trigger to his macro program on a different PC. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulimomanwe>Sulimo Manwe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 11:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hacking</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Pedi you said the guy would just put up afk when a GM zones in? that's pretty cool, I havent been following eq hacks for a while, but from my understanding he will need a version of showeq to detect the GM zoning in, then a script/trigger to his macro program on a different PC<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, remember that ShowEQ only sniffs out the stuff being sent to the client, so if ShowEQ can detect a GM in the zone, the client is certainly aware of that as well. All his script needs to do is monitor the memory location where zone spawns are held and when something comes in flagged as a GM, stop everything and turn on the AFK.<br>
<br>
What I don't get is why the GM didn't just zone in in their ultra-invisible mode, which as I understand it doesn't even transmit any packets to other clients in the same zone, it just listens to them, like passive sonar. Then he could have come up behind the gnome and observed everything and his script would be none the wiser. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=filanfyretracker>Filan Fyretracker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2063<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 12:08 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hacking</span><hr size=1> untill PoP ShowEQ was passive, verant/soe finally figured out how to break it though.  and showEQ was never hacking as technicly any data that enters your network is yours to do with what you see fit, id put it more on par with gameshark. <p><html><center><a href="mailto:filan@snet.net"><img 

